# Python 3.7 compatibility

CI matrix runs 3.8–3.13. All code must parse and run on Python 3.7. Stdlib only.

## Forbidden syntax (added after 3.7)

- Walrus operator `if (n := len(x)) > 5:` (3.8) — assign on a separate line
- Positional-only `def f(a, /, b):` (3.8)
- f-string self-documenting `f"{x=}"` (3.8)
- Builtin generics in annotations `list[int]`, `dict[str, int]` (3.9) — use `typing.List`, `typing.Dict`
- Union syntax `int | None` in annotations (3.10) — use `typing.Optional` / `typing.Union`
- `match`/`case` statements (3.10) — use `if`/`elif`
- Parenthesized context managers `with (open(a), open(b)):` (3.10)
- `except*` groups (3.11)

## Forbidden stdlib additions

- `functools.cache`, `functools.cached_property` (3.8/3.9) — use `functools.lru_cache(maxsize=None)` on functions
- `str.removeprefix` / `str.removesuffix` (3.9) — slice manually
- `importlib.metadata` (3.8), `zoneinfo` (3.9), `itertools.pairwise` (3.10)
- `typing.Protocol`, `typing.Literal`, `typing.TypedDict` (3.8) — avoid or guard
- `dict` union operators `d1 | d2`, `d |= d2` (3.9) — use `{**d1, **d2}` or `.update()`

## Allowed (3.7 has them)

`dataclasses`, ordered dicts by default, f-strings, `__future__.annotations`,
`contextlib.nullcontext`, `time.perf_counter_ns`.

When in doubt, check "Changed in version" / "New in version" notes in the Python docs.
